   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>2.8.1885 Sonntag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49289">Rigi Kaltbad</placeName>. August 2. 1885 Sunday.</p>
            <p>Got up at 7.45. and after breakfast read the papers and listened to the music on the
               Terrace till 10.30 when I had my bath. Afterwards walked with <persName key="104">Gee</persName> to the First and up a hill near it.
               We got caught in the rain though in coming home, and had to take shelter in
                  the First station. After Table d&#x2019;hôte again
               listened to the music and read and then walked to the
                  Känzli with <persName key="103">Mamma</persName>, <persName key="104">Gee</persName> and <persName key="1856">Lina</persName> who was very frightened
               at some cows; en plus the fog suddenly came down so we had to turn back. Drank milk
               at 5 and supped at 7. In between I numbered <name type="work" key="28586">the english
                  Roland</name>
               <note type="reg">
                  <persName key="103">Kessler</persName>
               </note>. After Supper there were very fine fireworks which <persName key="104">Gee</persName> came out to see in her nightgown. Afterwards a house was
               carried about with pictures of judges, priests etc. in a court of justice and some
               thing about a &#x201e;heiliges Strumpfband&#x201c; and &#x201e;3 Tage Arrest&#x201c; and Reporters.</p>
         </div>
